OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FITV News Scotland Correspondent Peter
OL,7,FSmith has been on the road with all of
OL,8,Fthe major Scottish parties who are
OL,9,Fvying for seats in this year's
OL,10,FHolyrood elections
OL,12,FScotland is heading to the polls on
OL,13,FMay 7, and ITV News has spent time on
OL,14,Fthe campaign trail with all six of the
OL,15,Fcountry's party leaders to hear their
OL,16,Fbig pitches for power.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FThe last Holyrood elections were held
OL,7,Fin 2021. Since then, Scotland has had
OL,8,Fthree first ministers, and the UK has
OL,9,Fhad three prime ministers. To say it
OL,10,Fhas been a rocky period is putting it
OL,11,Flightly.
OL,13,FThe SNP, in particular, has suffered
OL,14,Fserious turbulence.
OL,16,FFacing questions about scandals and
OL,17,Ftransparency, particularly the much-
OL,18,Fpublicised ferries fiasco, has all
OL,19,Ftaken its toll.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FJohn Swinney is the party's third
OL,7,Fleader in three years, but his pitch
OL,8,Fnow is about stability.
OL,10,F"I am a dependable person. I am
OL,11,Fsomeone to rely upon," he told ITV
OL,12,FNews.
OL,14,FBut he's defending a record of the SNP
OL,15,Fin government for almost 20 years now.
OL,17,FFor example, at the last election, his
OL,18,Fparty promised every child in Scotland
OL,19,Fa free laptop with internet access. It
OL,20,Fdidn't happen.
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FSwinney pointed to global events,
OL,7,Fciting Russia's invasion of Ukraine
OL,8,Fand the resulting inflation as factors
OL,9,Fbeyond the Scottish government's
OL,10,Fcontrol.
OL,12,FBut he mocks the idea that other
OL,13,Fparties can deliver a fresh start or
OL,14,F"change".
OL,16,F"My goodness, what a joke. Parties
OL,17,Foffering change," he said, pointing to
OL,18,FLabour's decision to cut winter fuel
OL,19,Fpayments shortly after winning the UK
OL,20,Fgeneral election.
OL,26,@xD@AOUyD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,F"The first thing they did was come in
OL,7,Fand take away winter fuel payments
OL,8,Ffrom pensioners."
OL,10,FAnd on independence, the issue that
OL,11,Fdefines his party above all else,
OL,12,FSwinney shows no sign of stopping the
OL,13,Fpush, even after the SNP's 2024
OL,14,Felection setback when Sturgeon had
OL,15,Fbilled the vote as a "de facto
OL,16,Freferendum" on the issue, and the
OL,17,Fparty subsequently suffered a
OL,18,Fhumiliating defeat.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,F"I believe fundamentally in the
OL,7,Fdemocratic right of the people of
OL,8,FScotland to decide their own future,"
OL,9,Fhe said.
OL,11,FReform is the new kid on the block.
OL,13,FIf the SNP represents continuity,
OL,14,FReform UK Scotland represents the
OL,15,Finsurgency, or, as they describe
OL,16,Fthemselves, "the disrupters".
OL,18,FIts Scottish leader, Malcolm Offord,
OL,19,Fis trying to build a distinctly
OL,20,FScottish version of the Farage brand.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@eO]xD@MOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FBut ITV News found some notable
OL,7,Fdaylight between Offord and his London
OL,8,Fleadership on their flagship issue.
OL,10,FWhen asked about immigration, Offord
OL,11,Fsaid Reform supported "controlled and
OL,12,Flegal immigration, bringing people in
OL,13,Fwho are skilled, who add to our
OL,14,Feconomy."
OL,16,FWhen asked to clarify if he means he
OL,17,Fis opposed to people coming in on
OL,18,Fboats but supports more skilled, legal
OL,19,Fimmigration coming to Scotland, he
OL,20,Fsaid "correct" and described it as
OL,21,F"good for the country".
OL,26,@sD@WOUvD@IO]|D@FOU|D@NO]}D@AOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FWhen it was put to him that Reform UK
OL,7,Fpolicy is to reduce legal immigration,
OL,8,Fand that his stance actually places
OL,9,Fhim closer to Keir Starmer than to
OL,10,FNigel Farage, he pushed back,
OL,11,Finsisting there was no contradiction.
OL,13,FBut after the interview ended, our
OL,14,Fmicrophones were still running. Offord
OL,15,Fcould be heard telling colleagues: "He
OL,16,Fthought he'd catch me out on Nigel
OL,17,F(Farage) saying we don't want any more
OL,18,Fimmigration at all, and I'm saying I'm
OL,19,Fokay with some skilled immigration.
OL,20,FBut I think I managed to deal with it.
OL,26,@wD@dOUyD@ApmyD@Hpn
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,F"Nigel, he's quite relaxed if we're
OL,7,Fnot right bang-on script. And
OL,8,Fsometimes he goes off script as well."
OL,10,FOfford isn't the only one going off
OL,11,Fmessage from the boss: Scottish Labour
OL,12,Fleader Anas Sarwar kicked off his
OL,13,Fcampaign calling for Keir Starmer to
OL,14,Fgo.
OL,16,FHe finds himself in an awkward
OL,17,Fposition. His party is in government
OL,18,Fat Westminster, but that has not
OL,19,Ftranslated into popularity north of
OL,20,Fthe border.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FDecisions like the winter fuel payment
OL,7,Fcut have damaged the UK government's
OL,8,Fstanding in Scotland, and Sarwar
OL,9,Fadmits this is something that's coming
OL,10,Fup with voters on the doorsteps.
OL,12,FAsked directly whether he had told the
OL,13,Fprime minister to stay away from the
OL,14,FScottish campaign trail, Sarwar was
OL,15,Fcandid: "I said this thing in public,
OL,16,Fthe best thing they can do is leave
OL,17,Fthe campaign to me, and they be at
OL,18,Ftheir desk doing the work of
OL,19,Fgovernment."
OL,26,@wD@IOU{D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FBut he's been criticised for the way
OL,7,Fhis campaign has gone. His rallying
OL,8,Fcry to wavering voters in this
OL,9,FHolyrood election was, "Hold your nose
OL,10,Fand vote Labour."
OL,12,FSarwar conceded it was not intended to
OL,13,Fbe the most inspirational slogan, but
OL,14,Fsaid many voters in this election
OL,15,Fwould be motivated by what they are
OL,16,Fangry about rather than what inspires
OL,17,Fthem.
OL,26,@qD@XOUrD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FThe Scottish Conservatives have a
OL,7,Fsimilar Westminster problem after a
OL,8,Fdecade of unexpected success in
OL,9,FScotland.
OL,11,FThe unionist vote that consolidated
OL,12,Faround them during the independence
OL,13,Fdebates is now diluted, and the polls
OL,14,Fare less kind.
OL,16,FLeader Russell Findlay, who has served
OL,17,Fas an MSP for five years, is trying to
OL,18,Fcreate distance between himself and
OL,19,Fthe UK Conservative government's
OL,20,Frecord.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,F"I'm not responsible for what the UK
OL,7,Fgovernment did," he said. "But 'Tory'
OL,8,Fto a lot of people in Scotland has bad
OL,9,Fassociations. It's associated with
OL,10,Fthings that didn't go right for us in
OL,11,Fgovernment." He acknowledged it would
OL,12,Fbe a problem at the doorstep.
OL,14,FThe Scottish Greens are the only party
OL,15,Fcontesting this election with co-
OL,16,Fleaders, Gillian Mackay and Ross Greer.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@PO]oD@[OUsD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FThey were previously in a power-
OL,7,Fsharing arrangement with Nicola
OL,8,FSturgeon's SNP, and are open to
OL,9,Fanother such deal to push green
OL,10,Fpolicies into law.
OL,12,FTheir platform includes banning horse
OL,13,Fracing, legalising and regulating
OL,14,Fdrugs, and, in a break with the
OL,15,Fcurrent direction of SNP foreign
OL,16,Fpolicy, refusing any cooperation with
OL,17,FDonald Trump's administration.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,F"There are other markets we should be
OL,7,Flooking at," said Mackay, when asked
OL,8,Fabout voters whose jobs depend on a
OL,9,Fgood relationship with the US
OL,10,Fpresident. "We should be making
OL,11,Fstronger alliances with Europe."
OL,13,FScottish Liberal Democrat leader Alex
OL,14,FCole-Hamilton is positioning his party
OL,15,Fas a partner for coalition government,
OL,16,Fbut with significant caveats.
OL,18,FHe has ruled out working with the SNP,
OL,19,FReform, and the Conservatives, which,
OL,20,Fas ITV News pointed out, rather
OL,21,Fnarrowly leaves Labour.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@LO]rD@LOUsD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31716
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,F"We'll look at the arithmetic," Cole-
OL,7,FHamilton said. "It would need to work
OL,8,Ffor our values. But I think this
OL,9,Fcountry is crying out for change."
OL,11,FDevolution came to Scotland in 1999
OL,12,Fwith the principle that the people of
OL,13,FScotland should have a direct say over
OL,14,Fmany of the decisions that affect
OL,15,Ftheir daily lives. It controls areas
OL,16,Fsuch as health, education, justice and
OL,17,Fhousing. These are the devolved issues.
OL,19,FDefence, foreign policy and most tax
OL,20,Fpowers are reserved for Westminster.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@_O]oD@POUqD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31717
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777107988
OL,3,COn the campaign trail with Scotland's
OL,4,Cleaders ahead of crucial elections
OL,6,FHolyrood also uses a hybrid voting
OL,7,Fsystem rather than the first-past-the-
OL,8,Fpost style used in UK general
OL,9,Felections.
OL,11,FVoters get two votes: one for a local
OL,12,Fconstituency MSP, and one for a
OL,13,Fregional party list. The system is
OL,14,Fspecifically designed to prevent any
OL,15,Fsingle party from winning an outright
OL,16,Fmajority, so coalition deals and
OL,17,Fminority governments are the norm
OL,18,Frather than the exception.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
